    "I ZSff0 BUSINESS AND FINANCE f 1 Industrial Conditions Good Says Mellon Department of Commerce Also Reports Busi L ness Prosperity With Increased Prices r By HARRY GUSACK The statement made by Secretaryof the Treasury Mellon yesterday that good industrial conditions now obtain in the United States is borne out by the Department of Com merce which today issues a survey of business conditions during the month of May Secretary of Commerce Hoovers reports that practically every idustry of which figures have been received showed greater actlTlty in May than in April Out of 42 pro ductlon movements reported 38 showed an increase and only four de clined compared with the montn I preceding Forward orders are In creasing and business again repre sents the picture of prosperity Prices on the average have not fallen below about 40 per cent over the prewar v level They are now nearly 60 per cent above that level No onf knows at what level prices finally will become stabilized but It Is believed that care should be used In placing large forward orders for raw materials at prices much above the present level The coal difficulties which are now In their fourteenth week"
